The Hatteras 58 Yacht Fisherman is essentially a 53 Motor Yacht with the addition of a 5-foot cockpit extension. She was introduced in 1970, just a year after the Hatteras 53 MY was launched, and she enjoyed a long and very successful production run during the next twelve years. The 58's cockpit makes her a more versatile and better handling boat than the 53 MY, and the additional fuel capacity results in a GREATER CRUISING RANGE. Belowdecks, her three-stateroom, galley-down floorplan is the same as the 53MY with the helm open to the salon and separate walk-in engine rooms. The Aft deck is sheltered by a bridge overhang and fitted with wing doors for wind and spray protection. She is powered with the Detroit Diesel 8V-71TI's which cruise at 16-17 knots. Still a popular yacht in spite of her age, resale values remain quite strong.

description: Up for sale is a 1967 Aquasport 22-2 Flatback. It was rigged with a 2007 Mercury 150 Optimax which currently has 360 hours and was recently serviced with a new oil pump installed and given a clean bill of health. I cruise at 4000 rpm at 30mph. The boat was just repainted Seafoam Green in December 2015. Also new within the last 6 months is the trolling motor (motor guide XI5), the Simrad GO7 chart plotter/fishfinder with navionics . I recently re-plumbed the live well adding a 1600 gph pump and new 1 1/8 flex hose. The front casting platform has three hatches, the middle hatch has a cast net bucket inside to keep your net out of the way while fishing. There is so much more to this boat but talking about it does not do it justice. A lot of money has gone into this classic boat and to restore one like this would cost a lot more than the asking price. I am including the aluminum trailer which is perfectly fit for the boat and pulls great. Please feel free to email or text any questions, phone calls are difficult to answer during the day but text and email I can reply quickly. If necessary I can call you in the evenings. The boat is titled and I do have the clean title in hand. Update: I have been flooded with questions on the boat so I decided to list out some of the other items on the boat. Engine: 2007 Mercury Optimax (2 stroke) 150hp. Hours: 360 Hydraulic steering Morse controls Porta Bracket adjustable height lift. Comes with a 3 blade aluminum prop and a 4 blade SS prop. Dual 8ft. power poles Hydraulic trim tabs, needs new relays. . .boat really does not need tabs but I left them on without installing new relays. Ping pong style scullpers. The hull was professionally painted 01/16 sea foam green. Motor Guide Xi5, bought in 03/2016. 24v system. 2 dedicated batteries for the trolling motor attached to a battery tender trickle charger. New Simrad Go7 chartplotter, sonar, downscan w/ navionics +. New Kenwood head unit, JVC amp, 12 inch sub, and 2 new Pioneer speakers. New Rule 1600 GPH live well pump and new 1 1/2" inlet line. 2 bank on board battery charger 2 batteries under the console for motor and house on a battery selector. Freshwater wash down pump and tank w/ hose under console. Marine radio under console LED front and rear deck lights 6 rod holders along the railing, 4 rod holders in seat/livewell 2 Seat post pads installed in front deck, included is a small wedge seat and an umbrella which was made to fit through the posts. The boat has 2 bilge pumps front and rear, both operate correctly. Large Bimini top Trailer: Dual axle Fastload aluminum rail trailer. 4 bunks custom fit for the boat. New front rollers, new strap, new chain, new guide posts and new lights.
